<P>
<U><B>Congressional Alcohol Fuels Caucus</B></U><BR>
The Alcohol Fuels Caucus has been a highly effective voice for the ethanol industry for more than 12 years.  Under the leadership of Rep. Dick Durbin (D-IL) and Jim Leach (R-IA), the Caucus has helped to build strong bipartisan support for the increased production and use of fuel ethanol.
<P>
With two members having been elected to the U.S. Senate, and several others having retired or been defeated, the Caucus will be seeking new membership.  The RFA will work to build membership as the 105th Congress convenes, and we urge all ethanol supporters to encourage their Member of Congress to join.
<P>
