<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#0000ff" VLINK="#ff0000" ALINK="#ff0000" TEXT="#000000" >
<H1>Ocean Seasons</H1>
<p>
<font size = +1>
The top map shows spring in the Northern Hemisphere.  Sea surface height is very low because cold, continental winds extract ocean heat throughout the winter. 
<p>
<center><img src=images/oc_seasons_small.gif></center>
<p>
The bottom map is from fall in the Northern Hemisphere.  Sea surface highs occur because of the expansion of the upper ocean water after it is heated throughout the summer.
</font>
<p>
<h5>
<address><a href=ed_workshop3.html#18>Back to "On-line" Workshop</a></address>
<ul>
</BODY>
