<HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#0000ff" VLINK="#ff0000" ALINK="#ff0000" TEXT="#000000" >
<H1>Causes of Seasonal Changes in the Oceans</H1>
<p>
<font size = +1>
<center><img src=images/ssv_top.gif></center>
In the Northern Hemisphere, the overall change in sea surface height between these seasons is very dramatic. Season-to-season changes in the Southern Hemisphere are much more moderate.
<p>
<center><img src=images/ssv_bottom.gif></center>
<p>
The "ocean seasons" look different in the Northern and Southern hemisphere because the higher percentage of ocean in the Southern Hemisphere moderates the ocean seasons.
<p>
<h5>
<address><a href=ed_workshop3.html#18>Back to "On-line" Workshop</a></address>
